snippet.textDisplay:
The US  has quite a few denominations above the $100 bill Linus.
The$500 bill has the fourth Chief Justice John Marshal, newer versions have William McKinley the 25th US President.
The $1000 bill has Alexander Hamilton with the newer version having Grover Cleveland. 
The $5000 bill has James Madison. 
US Bills up to $10,000 are still in private hands and where originally used for bank transfers. They still hold face value, but can be worth more due to rarity. 
The US $100,000 gold note was used by the Treasurer of the United States to the Federal Reserve banks against an equal amount of Gold, and are not legal to own.
